---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Research — Wright Lab">
  <main class="page">
    <span class="section-eyebrow">Research</span>
    <h1>Focus areas of the Wright Lab</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      The lab is organized around three interconnected lines of inquiry that together aim to map
      the molecular logic of cellular signaling in disease.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Proximity interaction networks</h2>
    <p>
      Constructing proximity interaction networks for key regulators of cellular proliferation,
      cell death, and cellular differentiation.
    </p>
    <img src="/images/focus-1-neighborhood.jpg" alt="Protein neighborhood — a central highlighted protein with proximal partners shown as a network of connected dots" class="research-image" />
    <p class="muted"><em>Full description coming soon.</em></p>

    <h2>2. Novel proximity enzymes</h2>
    <p>
      Developing novel proximity-labeling enzymes to capture post-translational modifications
      in complex biological matrices.
    </p>
    <img src="/images/focus-2-toolkit.jpg" alt="Cartographer's toolkit — a surveying instrument over a molecular landscape, representing different proximity-labeling enzymes" class="research-image" />
    <p class="muted"><em>Full description coming soon.</em></p>

    <h2>3. Reagents &amp; methods for cell biology</h2>
    <p>
      Optimizing cell biology reagents and methods to interrogate the molecular function of
      protein complexes.
    </p>
    <img src="/images/focus-3-resolution.jpg" alt="Resolution levels — nested concentric zoom from cell population to single protein complex" class="research-image" />
    <p class="muted"><em>Full description coming soon.</em></p>
  </main>

  <style>
    .research-image {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 900px;
      height: auto;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(15, 44, 46, 0.10);
      display: block;
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
